<br>
Since the shaman in question was higher level, and had the piece on him, I figured, sure, at least I'll see where what it takes to bring him down.<br>
<br>
After the fight, while congradulating him on his piece, I was told to loot the torch!  <br>
<br>
So I just want to assure you all that even if the shaman does do  his turn in, the torch CAN and DID drop. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=perilbane>Perilbane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 312<br> <font color=#333333>(2/17/03 5:58:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1628.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Neh`Ashiir, the torch, and Shaman Epic turn in</span><hr size=1> I just have abominable luck against Phinny and Neh'Ashir. <br>
<br>
12 Neh'Ashir kills and no torch<br>
26 (that's right... 26) Phinny kills and no staff.<br>
<br>
I have not lost a roll ... they simply haven't dropped for me.<br>
This isn't a complaint. I gave up on complaining. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
I just seem to have just about the most rotten luck imagineable with these 2.<br>
<br>
